        <p>In this scenario, paying 0.75% instead of 0.03% doesn't sound terrible at first. But over 30 years, that 0.72% difference costs you over <strong>$14,000</strong> in lost wealth on a mere $10k investment.</p>

        <h2>Interactive ETF Fee Calculator</h2>
        <p>See the impact for yourself. Enter your expected investment, time horizon, and the expense ratio to see how much wealth is lost to fees.</p>

